<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="256" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,1253,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,312,1434,1460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Flagellomeres differentiated, cervical region fairly long (unclear in 
<taxonomicName box="[487,632,1471,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Archizelmiridae" genus="Archimelzira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[487,632,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">Archimelzira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); wing with
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,1253,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">
Sc incomplete, long, extending to level of 
<emphasis box="[623,663,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">r-m</emphasis>
; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[698,706,1526,1540]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">1</subScript>
short, extending to level of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[409,434,1562,1576]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">1+2</subScript>
furcation; Rs base transverse; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[155,181,1598,1612]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">4+5</subScript>
unforked; basal part of M absent; CuP incomplete; anal lobe large, well-developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,1253,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,305,1653,1679]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">Remarks.</emphasis>
Most of the diagnostic characters are synapomorphies. The long Sc and transverse base of Rs
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,1253,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="256">are plesiomorphic. The large anal lobe is a trait of unclear polarity.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
